    <etym xml:lang="ru">Хотя есть соблазн рассматривать это слово как модификацию слова <ref
            type="xr" target="#entry_carm"/> ʼкожаʼ, ʼшкураʼ, однако многочисленные соответствия в
        кавказских языках заставляют думать о субстратном происхождении; ср. <mentioned
            xml:lang="x-vaynakh"><lang/><w>čʼor</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="x-vaynakh"
                ><w>čʼorg</w><gloss><q>кожица</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="x-vaynakh"><w/><gloss><q>скорлупа</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned
            xml:lang="lez"><lang/><w>čʼar</w><note type="comment" xml:lang=""/><note type="comment"
                xml:lang=""/><gloss><q>сливки</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="lez"
                ><w/><note type="comment" xml:lang=""/><note type="comment" xml:lang=""
                    /><gloss><q>бумага</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="sva"
                ><lang/><w>čxvar-</w><gloss><q>кора</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="ka"><lang/><w>cʼeri</w><gloss><q>кора орехового дерева</q></gloss></mentioned>
                (<bibl><ref target="#ref_Беридзе"/></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/><note
                type="comment" xml:lang="">() </note><note type="comment" xml:lang="">()
                </note><w>čʼari</w><gloss><q>чешуяя змеи</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Чкония"/></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="ab"
                    ><lang/><w>a-cʼarš</w><gloss><q>подкладка</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="ab"><w>a-c˳a</w><gloss><q>кожа</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned
            xml:lang="abq"><lang/><w>cʼa</w><gloss><q>кожа</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="uby"><lang/><w>čʼe</w><gloss><q>кожа</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="uby"><w/><gloss><q>кора</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="uby"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>скорлупа</q></gloss></mentioned>, . Сюда же, очевидно, <mentioned
            xml:lang="ka"><lang/><w>*cʼari</w></mentioned> в <mentioned xml:lang="ka"
                ><lang/><w>ze-cʼari</w><gloss><q>простыня</q></gloss></mentioned>, буквально
        „верхняя (<mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/><w>ze</w></mentioned>) оболочка (<mentioned
            xml:lang="ka"><lang/><w>cʼari</w></mentioned>)“.%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"
                /><biblScope>314</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
    <etym xml:lang="en">Although it is tempting to consider this word as a modification of the word
            <ref type="xr" target="#entry_carm"/> ʼskinʼ, ʼfellʼ, however numerous correspondences
        in Caucasian languages make us think of the substrate origin of the word; cf. <mentioned
            xml:lang="x-vaynakh"><lang/><w>čʼor</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="x-vaynakh"
                ><w>čʼorg</w><gloss><q>peel</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-vaynakh"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>shuck</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="lez"
                ><lang/><w>čʼar</w><note type="comment" xml:lang=""/><note type="comment"
                xml:lang=""/><gloss><q>fleet</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="lez"
                ><w/><note type="comment" xml:lang=""/><note type="comment" xml:lang=""
                    /><gloss><q>paper</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="sva"
                ><lang/><w>čxvar-</w><gloss><q>bark</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="ka"><lang/><w>cʼeri</w><gloss><q>walnut bark</q></gloss></mentioned>
                (<bibl><ref target="#ref_Беридзе"/></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/><note
                type="comment" xml:lang="">() </note><note type="comment" xml:lang="">()
                </note><w>čʼari</w><gloss><q>snake's scale</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Чкония"/></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="ab"
                    ><lang/><w>a-cʼarš</w><gloss><q>backing</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="ab"><w>a-c˳a</w><gloss><q>skin</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned
            xml:lang="abq"><lang/><w>cʼa</w><gloss><q>skin</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="uby"><lang/><w>čʼe</w><gloss><q>skin</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="uby"><w/><gloss><q>bark</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="uby"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>shuck</q></gloss></mentioned>, . Obviously, also here <mentioned
            xml:lang="ka"><lang/><w>*cʼari</w></mentioned> in <mentioned xml:lang="ka"
                ><lang/><w>ze-cʼari</w><gloss><q>bedsheet</q></gloss></mentioned>, literally “upper
            (<mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/><w>ze</w></mentioned>) cover (<mentioned xml:lang="ka"
                ><lang/><w>cʼari</w></mentioned>)“.%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"
                /><biblScope>314</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
